column1: Which team will win the 2019 NBA Western Conference Championship?
column5: ['Golden State Warriors', 'Denver Nuggets', 'Portland Trail Blazers', 'Houston Rockets', 'Utah Jazz', 'Oklahoma City Thunder', 'San Antonio Spurs', 'Los Angeles Clippers']

column6: Portland would have to win all four of the remaining games.
Updating odds after end of semis. Current crowd: Warrior (67%), Rockets (19%), Nuggets (6%), and Portland (4%). Other teams still registering @ 1% each.
I give the Rockets Warriors side of the bracket 70% winning the west. Rest splits between Spurs Nuggets and Thunder.
In the NBA, teams that go up 2-0 in a 7 game series win 93.5% of the time, because of this I am writing off the Utah Jazz and the Oklahoma City Thunder.
